		<h3>Minutes of SAC Meeting Held on 30.01.2012 at MRC</h3></a></div>
</div>
</div> <!-- /widget-header -->

<div class="widget-content">
<div id="collapsemainone" class="collapse"><div class="accordion-inner">
ATTENDED BY: &nbsp;
SSAC, SGS, HAS, CAS (A), CAS (L), CCAS, AAS<br><br>
SAC MEMBERS PRESENT: &nbsp;
31 (out of 49); (Attendance sheet with SSAC)<br><br>
Dean of Students also attended the meeting<br><br>
VENUE: &nbsp;
MRC, Central Library, IITM (5pm-8pm)<br><br>
MINUTES:<br>
		
		<div class="accordion" id="accordion2">
				<div class="accordion-group">
						<div class="accordion-heading">
								<a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseOne">
										Internet Connectivity
								</a>
						</div>
						<div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-body collapse">
								<div class="accordion-inner">
										Academic Affairs Secretary will form and head an ad-hoc committee to look into all the internet connectivity issues. The committee will make a report and submit recommendations to the concerned authorities.
								</div>
						</div>
				</div><!--accordion-group-->
				<div class="accordion-group">
						<div class="accordion-heading">
								<a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseTwo">
										Placement Statistics
								</a>
						</div>
						<div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-body collapse">
								<div class="accordion-inner">
										Academic Affairs Secretary presented the placement statistics. He is requested to add data on students going for higher studies in the statistics after the admission processes in foreign and Indian universities are over.
								</div>
						</div>
				</div><!--accordion-group-->
				<div class="accordion-group">
						<div class="accordion-heading">
								<a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseThree">
										Hostel Nights
								</a>
						</div>
						<div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-body collapse">
								<div class="accordion-inner">
										An appeal was made to relax the time restriction for girls to be present in boys hostel during hostel nights from the 9pm to 12am. SAC passed this appeal and will forward the appeal to concerned authorities.
								</div>
						</div>
				</div><!--accordion-group-->
				<div class="accordion-group">
						<div class="accordion-heading">
								<a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseFour">
										HOLI (8th March 2012)
								</a>
						</div>
						<div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-body collapse">
								<div class="accordion-inner">
										Request for a holiday on the occasion of Holiday (8th March12) was made and SAC passed the motion. The request will now be made on behalf of students to the concerned authorities.
								</div>
						</div>
				</div><!--accordion-group-->
				<div class="accordion-group">
						<div class="accordion-heading">
								<a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseFive">
										Shaastra/Saarang Rescheduling
								</a>
						</div>
						<div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-body collapse">
								<div class="accordion-inner">
										CCAS. CAS (A) and CAS (L) presented 5 possible scenarios for scheduling Shaastra and Saarang. With no major objections and recommendations from the SAC, they will be presenting the scenarios on behalf of the student community to the concerned authorities.
								</div>
						</div>
				</div><!--accordion-group-->
		</div>
</div>
</div>
